summary: Tony listens to Peter cry from the other side of the bathroom door.  He sits, knees drawn to his chest, flinching as Peter sobs...
body:
Tony listens to Peter cry from the other side of the bathroom door. 

He sits, knees drawn to his chest, flinching as Peter sobs on the bathroom floor. It aches in a way Tony hadn’t known was possible. He yearns to break open the lock, to hug Peter tight and never let go, to chase away whatever was hurting him. Briefly, he wonders if this is how his mother or Edwin Jarvis felt every time he locked his own bathroom door, drunk and exhausted in a way no one could help him with.

To not be able to comfort Peter, his kid, was unfathomable, unnatural. His heart twists and clenches as Peter sobs; he’s half-tempted to get a gauntlet and break down the door, but Peter had requested that Tony leave him alone.

Unlike his own parents, Tony abides by Peter’s wishes. He won’t break into the bathroom. He’ll sit on the floor and wait until Peter’s ready.

He fixes things, but he can’t fix this. Can’t fix the pain coursing its way through Peter’s veins. All he can do is offer comfort. A tight hug, a hand that will run through Peter’s curls. 

For now, he sits on the floor and waits.

summary: What about a discussion between May and Tony and Stephen ? Peter already lost two fathers, what if she asks them not to die, for...
question: What about a discussion between May and Tony and Stephen ? Peter already lost two fathers, what if she asks them not to die, for the sake of Peter, so he doesn't have to go through the pain of losing two other dads ?
answer:
The air was tense in the room. Barely anyone could breath after the words had been said. Slowly May let go of a heavy sigh.

She watched them closely at every movement they made. The paper hidden from view clutched hopefully under the table russled in the soundless space.

“I understand.” She finally answered keeping her voice from shaking.

“May please, you don’t have to agree if you do want to. He’s still your nephew.” Tony said putting a hand over her shoulder. He didn’t want to upset her.

Stephen didn’t say much but his nervous expression spoke volumes.

“I know, it just I knew this day would come. We raised him since he was still so little and I doubt he even remembers much of his birth parents. He will always be mine but I knew he needs a father or fathers in this case.” May smiled for a moment but then she bit her lip in worry.

“The we have plenty of room your you to stay with us. You won’t be apart from him.” Stephen pitched in trying to keep her calm.

“I’ll think about that but more importantly the papers.” She held out her hand as Stephen passed her the adoption form. “But before I sign you have to promise me something.”

“Anything.” Tony said immediately. He’d give the world for this, for Peter.

“Peter has lost so many people in his life. Father, mother and uncle. I’m the last parent figure he has and I didn’t have a real choice in the matter but Peter is my heart even though. This choice you’re making is the biggest in your lives. So you better be sure.” May ordered glaring at bother men.

“I’d be lost without Peter. He’s probably the best thing that happened to me. All I want is for him to be safe and happy with us. And also if he wants, take over the company when I’m too old and crusty to bother with it.” Tony said taking May’s hand.

“I haven’t been with Peter as long as Tony, mostly because Tony didn’t introduce us until a few years after we started dating. But all that time we spent together while trapped in the soul stone changed that. He never left my side as talked about every little thing he remembered about the outside. He said he didn’t want to forget what matter most. Even after he got out he continued to it. He reminds me everyday to appreciate life and the present. He means so much to me as well.” Stephen said almost silently, he wasn’t good at expressing how he felt but he was so happy to have Peter in his life.

“Good, so promise me you’ll stay alive out there. Peter..he…he can’t take another heartbreak. He nearly lost it with Ben and losing you of all people would destroy him” May said in a warning tone.

“I understand. I can’t really promise you that though. If push comes to shove and he’s in danger, I may have to risk it all. I’m sure he knows that too. I can promise that what I can control(like my drinking and experimental tech) won’t be what takes me from him. And should things go tits up at least we have a doctor in the family.” Tony laughed at the end.

“I can promise that I’ll preserve my life for Peter sake. Im not nearly as reckless as Tony but I still have dangerous tasks I must face. For Peter however i will take extra caution.” Stephen agreed handing May the pen.

May smiled at both men and soon to be fathers as she signed the paper. She hugged them both since now they would be family in more then words alone. She had not doubt they would give Peter the world and go to the ends of earth for him so May was satisfied.
